Input :- A number n 
         n1,n2,.....n Integers representing elements of an array
Process :- Find the span of the array. 
Output :- Print the span of the array.

Pre-requisite :- Span of the array is the difference between the largest and smallest element of the array.

Example :- 

          Input :-
          n = 6
          array = [33, 83, 29, 10, 1, 99]
          
          Output :-
          span = 99-1 = 98
